# Error Handling Rules

## Backend
- Always use NestJS built-in exceptions: HttpException, BadRequestException, InternalServerErrorException
- Never return error objects from controllers — throw exceptions
- validation_error scenarios: throw BadRequestException (or HttpException 400) with a descriptive message
- system_error scenarios: throw Error; let the global exception filter map unhandled errors to 500 if one is added
- Always call Sentry.captureException with the thrown error for system_error type (in the handler that catches the simulated failure)
- Global exception filter (when present) must map all unhandled errors to 500 with a safe message

## Frontend
- useMutation onError: show a toast or inline error message — never swallow errors silently
- validation_error (400): show the error message from the response body
- system_error (500): show a generic "Something went wrong" message to the user
- Network errors: show a short connectivity or retry hint; do not fail silently
